06/05/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Authorities arrested three foreigners who allegedly stayed illegally in the country in a two-day joint action involving police and the State Information and Protection Agency (SIPA).
The operation wrapped up on Tuesday (May 5th).
The three are reportedly foreign-born Muslims who fought in the 1992-1995 conflict.
Police arrested two Monday night in the Zenica-Doboj region and detained the third late Tuesday.
All three are now in the hands of the immigration service.
(Dnevni Avaz, B92 - 06/05/09;
Reuters, RTS - 05/05/09)
